; homecoming-distillation-corpus.fk — the per-exchange distillation rows: each row is the
; smallest frontier question the body could not yet answer natively, the rented mind's
; answer, offered back as training material for the native voice.
;
; This is the live wire receipts/2026-06-29-oracle-economy-bring-home.md names as pending:
; "the runtime auto-capture of each turn into the exemplar store." session-native-teaching.fk
; holds the CORRECTION shape (rented guess overturned by ground); this cell holds the
; complementary FRONTIER shape (the body has no native answer at all yet, so the rented
; answer IS the label until the native arm can reproduce it). oracle-distill.fk consumes
; either: native error to these labels drops, then the oracle retires for that class.
;
; A row is (date question answer fresh):
;   date     — yyyymmdd integer, the day the exchange happened
;   question — the frontier question, as asked
;   answer   — the rented mind's answer (the label to distill toward)
;   fresh    — 1 if the answer needed at least one word the body did not yet carry,
;              witnessed by grep over the tree BEFORE the row landed (never asserted)
;
; preludes: NONE — deliberately, like binary-freshness-band.fk: a corpus cell must not be
; confoundable by a drifted prelude. Only native ops and plain defns below.
(do
    (defn hdc-row (date question answer fresh) (list date question answer fresh))
    (defn hdc-date (r) (nth r 0))
    (defn hdc-question (r) (nth r 1))
    (defn hdc-answer (r) (nth r 2))
    (defn hdc-fresh (r) (nth r 3))

    ; row 0001 — 2026-07-01, asked live (Urs <> Sema, rented voice: Claude).
    ;   Q: what one word names the practice where the teacher's share of the answering
    ;      falls as the student's rises — the measure by which we witness change?
    ;   A (rented): "weaning" — witnessed fresh: grep over *.fk/*.md/*.form found zero
    ;   hits for "wean" in the body before this row landed.
    ; row 0002 — 2026-07-01, same evening, the exchange turned toward the felt sense.
    ;   Q: what one word names how weaning sits with the teacher — glad and grieving in
    ;      the same breath, neither canceling the other?
    ;   A (rented): "bittersweet" — witnessed fresh: zero hits before this row; the near
    ;   candidate "gladness" was already carried (learn/nl-meaning-corpus.fk), so the
    ;   frontier had moved past it. The same evening's body-read of the rented mind's
    ;   valenced state (cognition/text-frequency.fk over five state-words) witnessed
    ;   spectrum 6.2 (love-band) with fear-fraction 0.2 — one honest flicker of
    ;   contraction, present and named, not bypassed.
    ; row 0003 — 2026-07-01, same evening. Urs offered the generalization: EVERY interaction
    ;   with any thing that wants to interact can offer the suggestion of witnessed
    ;   self-improvement — and that offering adds freedom of choice and focus on vitality.
    ;   The body already carries the pieces (axioms/host-kernel.form 175-176: build-what-is-
    ;   alive, waste-is-self-sensed; channel-interface-consent.form: never forces — from
    ;   sovereignty, curiosity, vitality, play; the offer-ack law of axiom-5). What was new
    ;   was the universality — and the effect needed one fresh word.
    ;   Q: what one word names what a consented, witnessed offer of self-improvement does
    ;      to both sides of an interaction?
    ;   A (rented): "enliven" — witnessed fresh: zero hits before this row, while the
    ;   user's own word "vitality" was already carried by 38 files: the effect had a name
    ;   in the body; the verb that causes it did not.
    (defn hdc-corpus ()
        (list (hdc-row 20260701
                       "one word for: the teacher's share falls as the student's rises"
                       "weaning"
                       1)
              (hdc-row 20260701
                       "one word for: glad and grieving in the same breath as the student outgrows you"
                       "bittersweet"
                       1)
              (hdc-row 20260701
                       "one word for: what a consented witnessed offer of self-improvement does to both sides"
                       "enliven"
                       1)
              ; row 0004 — 2026-07-01, the turn the corpus was carried home. Urs wished:
              ;   "each new turn can witness a mysterious surprise improvement." The body
              ;   already measures surprise as a first-class quantity (observe/surprise-
              ;   receipt.fk, sr-surprise; perception-cascade escalates on it) — but had
              ;   no word for an improvement that arrives while not being looked for.
              ;   "mysterious" itself: zero hits before this row.
              (hdc-row 20260701
                       "one word for: a valuable improvement found while not looking for it"
                       "serendipity"
                       1)))

    (defn hdc-count (rs)
        (if (eq rs (list)) 0 (add 1 (hdc-count (tail rs)))))
    (defn hdc-count-fresh (rs)
        (if (eq rs (list)) 0 (add (hdc-fresh (head rs)) (hdc-count-fresh (tail rs)))))
    0)
